title: Drake Brings Out Future for 'What a Time to Be Alive' Tracks at Austin City Limits
text:
Comments Drizzy and Future perform 'Where Ya At' from the latter's 'DS2' album in addition to 'Jump Man' and 'Big Ring' from their joint mixtape. 
Drake reunited with his " What a Time to Be Alive " collaborator Future during his headlining set at the 2015 Austin City Limits. The two rappers teamed up for some songs off their joint mixtape as they closed out the second day of weekend one of the festival. Future first did some of his own hits like "F**k Up Some Commas" and "Trap N***as" before tackling "Where Ya At", his collaboration with Drake off his latest solo album " DS2 ". They went on to treat the crowd to the first live performances of "Jump Man" and "Big Rings" from "WATTBA". Following Future's appearance at his set, Drake took to Instagram to thank his "brother." He posted a black-and-white photo and wrote alongside it, "Thank you to my brother @future for giving Austin a moment." A photo posted by champagnepapi (@champagnepapi) on Oct 3, 2015 at 8:48pm PDT In addition to the tracks off his and Future's chart-topping mixtape, Drizzy played a number of his other hits like "Started From the Bottom", "Hotline Bling", "Back to Back" and "Energy" as well as covers of Fetty Wap 's "My Way", Nicki Minaj 's "Truffle Butter" and I LOVE MAKONNEN 's "Tuesday".
